## How to style sort

Styles from the `material/sort` package can be customized using the `sort-overrides` mixin.  This mixin accepts a set of tokens that control how the components will look, either for the entire app or under a specific selector. For example:

```
@use '@angular/material' as mat;

// Customize the entire app. Change :root to your selector if you want to scope the styles.
:root {
  @include mat.sort-overrides((
    arrow-color: orange,
  ));
}
```

You can find the full list of supported mixins and tokens below.

